Parliament, Wednesday, 25 September 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Tourism will undertake an oversight visit to KwaZulu-Natal from 26th to 28th September 2019. Members of the media are invited to the programme on Thursday, 26th September 2019. Details of Thursday’s programme: 
	10h00 - 11h00 Site visit at Howick Falls
	11h05 - 13h00 Stakeholder engagement at Howick Agricultural Hall
	13h15 – 14h30 Media briefing and Q & A session at The Farmer’s Daughter ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON TOURISM, MR SUPRA MAHUMAPELO. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sureshinee Govender
